subSubSection.paragraph:
KNM WS-12866 is a large fragment of the crown of a large lower i2 (diameters: 42 × 24). In its unworn part, the cross-section is amygdaloidal, i.e., the dorsal face is as convex as the enamel-covered ventral one. It is likely from a male individual, while the much worn i2 WS- 12864 (
Fig. 3L
), which preserves its very long root, is much smaller (26.5 × 17) and therefore probably represents a female.
